  <data-orientation>
    <data-orientation-item>
      <simple-id uuid='{CDD08AC7-214F-4A0B-89BD-D8ACB03F31BD}' />
      <desc>Total annualized recurring revenue across all active accounts, calculated from the most recent day of data. The single number a leadership team checks first to gauge overall business size.</desc>
    </data-orientation-item>
    <data-orientation-item>
      <simple-id uuid='{81D02621-26C8-4849-BE79-1FC705E8F310}' />
      <desc>Average annual revenue per paying account. Calculated as total ARR divided by the count of accounts currently generating revenue. Useful for tracking whether growth is coming from more customers or bigger customers.</desc>
    </data-orientation-item>
    <data-orientation-item>
      <simple-id uuid='{F02CE2FB-DD89-429F-8964-1F9317F63CAC}' />
      <desc>Annual recurring revenue lost to cancellations in the trailing 90 days, broken down by plan tier. Shows which customer segment is contributing the most to revenue attrition.</desc>
    </data-orientation-item>
    <data-orientation-item>
      <simple-id uuid='{C3F5038C-7182-4811-B76E-D3BD973517BB}' />
      <desc>Net monthly change in recurring revenue, month by month, shown as a bar chart. Indigo bars mark months where growth outpaced losses; red bars mark months where cancellations outweighed new and expanded revenue.</desc>
    </data-orientation-item>
    <data-orientation-item>
      <simple-id uuid='{EADF60F9-187D-4DC0-85F1-77BA45F355FE}' />
      <desc>Percentage of each monthly signup cohort still active in every subsequent month, read left to right. Green cells indicate strong retention; red cells indicate cohorts that have thinned out. Reveals exactly when customers tend to leave.</desc>
    </data-orientation-item>
    <data-orientation-item>
      <simple-id uuid='{C33BB060-E6AF-41CC-9FA3-E1386A9E315C}' />
      <desc>Monthly recurring revenue at the end of each calendar month since launch, shown as an area chart. Tracks the company&apos;s overall growth trend across its full operating history.</desc>
    </data-orientation-item>
    <data-orientation-item>
      <simple-id uuid='{79A14FA8-82A6-42D9-95E1-2110CB09314D}' />
      <desc>Net change in monthly recurring revenue over the trailing 30 days — every dollar gained from new and expanding customers minus every dollar lost to cancellations. Positive means the business grew last month; negative means losses outpaced gains.</desc>
    </data-orientation-item>
    <data-orientation-item>
      <simple-id uuid='{26FF20E4-7EE3-4C78-AF76-AA478E254CE2}' />
      <desc>Average daily time customers spend inside the product, in minutes, over the trailing 30 days. A simple proxy for product engagement and stickiness.</desc>
    </data-orientation-item>
    <data-orientation-item>
      <simple-id uuid='{FB189B3B-6D88-4C6E-88FD-3F41B64169CB}' />
      <desc>Count of cancellation events grouped by the reason the customer gave, ranked from most to least common. The dashed line marks the average count across all reasons, making it easy to spot which causes are above or below normal.</desc>
    </data-orientation-item>
    <data-orientation-item>
      <simple-id uuid='{D4B76EBB-8734-4295-8321-FBE06ED7AAC6}' />
      <desc>Average hours to resolve a support ticket, broken down by ticket priority level. Sorted from most to least urgent, this chart exposes whether the support team&apos;s response speed actually matches how urgent each ticket really is.</desc>
    </data-orientation-item>
    <data-orientation-item>
      <simple-id uuid='{CB431AA5-E90D-4A08-8EF3-C6E3224406DE}' />
      <desc>RavenStack — Revenue &amp; Retention Command Center

An executive view of a subscription software business&apos;s financial health and customer retention. Combines headline revenue metrics, growth trends, cohort survival rates, churn drivers, and support performance into a single screen — built to be read top to bottom in under two minutes by someone with no data background.</desc>
    </data-orientation-item>
  </data-orientation>
</workbook>
